      "writtenOn": "2026-07-24T08:10:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "hi Striman\nCan you please confirm which spec version you are checking? This implementation is based on DSP0257 1.0.0.\n\nIn DSP0257 1.0.0, Table 7 defines the FRU Record Table as:\nFRU Record Data (1 or more) + Pad + CRC\n\nThere is no partial FRU Record Data in 1.0 — the pad and CRC-32 apply to the complete table only, so no per-chunk CRC exists in this layout. Partial FRU Record Data is introduced only in DSP0257 2.0, which is not backward compatible with 1.0. To my knowledge OpenBMC\u0027s FRU support is entirely 1.0 today",
      "revId": "82885751a6c44a5896aaa7b8af2c5560b3c964e7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "fb0dba62_0ac013e9",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
        "patchSetId": 5
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 1001853
      },
      "writtenOn": "2026-07-24T11:32:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My bad, I was looking at v2.0.0 in my previous comment. But I\u0027ve just checked DSP0257 v1.0.0, and I still think each response has its own padding and CRC.\n\n`DSP0257 Version 1.0.0, 9.2.3 GetFRURecordTable`:\n\n\u003e This command is defined to allow the FRU Record Table data to be transferred using a **sequence of one or more command/response messages**. When more than one command is used to transfer the FRU Record Table, the **response messages** contain the non-overlapping contiguous **portions** of FRU RecordTable **as defined in Table 7**.\n\n---\n\n\u003e There is no partial FRU Record Data in 1.0\n\n\nI\u0027m not sure that I understand you. If this is about \u0027chunk\u0027 - I didn\u0027t mean partial internal data, I meant that `FRU Record Data (1 or more)` in Table 7 represents part of FRU table (which I called \u0027chunk\u0027).\n\n\u003e FRU Record Data (1 or more) + Pad + CRC\n\u003e the pad and CRC-32 apply to the complete table only\n\nDoes it contradict the spec? Because `FRU Record Data (1 or more)` is not equal to full FRU table. It may be just part of table (`10.1 Multipart Transfers` in 1.0.0). Am I wrong?",
      "parentUuid": "6ae3d156_7149b018",
      "revId": "82885751a6c44a5896aaa7b8af2c5560b3c964e7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d35d3c26_80019134",
        "filename": "/PATCHSET_LEVEL",
